&gt; What I&#39;ve found works best (at least in the situations I have
&gt; encountered) is to have the main parser actually delegate to a number of
&gt; sub-parsers. That is, if for example one thing you need to parse is a
&gt; color specification, extract that logic into a ColorParser. That makes
&gt; it both easier to test in isolation, easier to read and maintain and
&gt; more reusable.
